  "prompt": "What are the duties of the Librarian of Congress? What day-to-day activities does the job entail?",
  "response": "The Librarian of Congress is a high-level appointed position responsible for overseeing the Library of Congress, the largest library in the world. Here are the key duties and activities:\n\nPrimary Responsibilities:\n1. Overall management of the Library of Congress\n2. Serving as the head of the largest library and research institution in the United States\n3. Appointing library officials and staff\n4. Developing and implementing library policies and strategies\n5. Representing the library to Congress, other government agencies, and the public\n\nKey Duties:\n1. Preserving and expanding the library's vast collection of books, manuscripts, recordings, and digital materials\n2. Overseeing copyright registration for the United States\n3. Promoting literacy and educational programs\n4. Managing the library's budget and resources\n5. Developing digital archiving and access strategies\n6. Advising Congress on information and research matters\n\nDay-to-Day Activities:\n1. Administrative meetings and strategic planning\n2. Reviewing acquisition proposals for new materials\n3. Attending congressional hearings and briefings\n4. Meeting with donors, researchers, and international library representatives\n5. Overseeing digital transformation initiatives\n6. Reviewing and approving major research and preservation projects\n\nThe position requires extensive knowledge of library science, information management, and government operations.",
